<P>And what added to my afflictions, were the revilings of tho&s;e hardened wretches that were there before me; &s;coffing, what Mrs. Flanders catched in the trap at la&s;t, &s;urely the devil had helped me, or I had been in New|gate long before. Then they welcomed me to the place, and then called for brandy, and drank to me, &s;ay|ing &s;urely I had money, tho they had none.</P>
